# LAMMPS Input File  (figure: solid-liquid interface evolution vs temperature)
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# Build ONE solid-liquid two-phase cell of fcc Al (Mendelev potential), then
# hold a copy of it at three temperatures -- above, at, and below the melting
# point -- and snapshot the interface at four times each.  Below Tm the solid
# (right) grows into the liquid (left); above Tm it melts; near Tm it barely
# moves.  Atoms are colored by common-neighbor analysis of the INHERENT
# structure (a brief minimization per snapshot removes thermal noise, since
# near Tm the instantaneous structures of hot solid and liquid overlap).
#
# Designed to run in parallel (e.g. mpirun -np 64 lmp -in evolution.lmp).
# The three temperatures may need a few-kelvin adjustment to straddle this
# cell's Tm; the segment length (run NNN) sets how far the interface moves
# between frames.  Assemble the 12 PNGs with, e.g.:
#   montage evo_970_*.png evo_930_*.png evo_890_*.png -tile 4x3 -geometry +4+4 evolution.png

# ---------- build the two-phase cell ----------
units metal
atom_style atomic
boundary p p p
lattice fcc 4.05
Lattice spacing in x,y,z = 4.05 4.05 4.05
region box block 0 10 0 10 0 40          # bigger cross-section for a clean interface
create_box 1 box
Created orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (40.5 40.5 162)
  2 by 2 by 16 MPI processor grid
create_atoms 1 box
Created 16000 atoms
  using lattice units in orthogonal box = (0 0 0) to (40.5 40.5 162)
  create_atoms CPU = 0.003 seconds
mass 1 26.98
pair_style eam/fs
pair_coeff * * ../Al_mm.eam.fs Al
Reading eam/fs potential file ../Al_mm.eam.fs with DATE: 2007-06-11
velocity all create 800.0 7654 mom yes rot yes
timestep 0.002
thermo 10000

fix eq all npt temp 800.0 800.0 0.2 x 0 0 2 y 0 0 2 z 0 0 2 couple xy
run 15000
